reviews.text: Waits are incredibly long, so plan ahead and make sure you're in good company! Food is delicious the restaurants unique character is part of the experience. Don't go if you expect to be treated like a king. The wait staff has never been outwardly rude, but they have definitely been annoyed with the chef ;)
Portions are huge, which yields above average prices. Usually takes a while for dinner, so plan to spend some time here. All of the rolls I've had here have been pretty delicious.

The food was fantastic and delicious. Just read all the signs when you come in and understand you will wait a long time. Don't rate something down because you didn't understand the culture of the restaurant. I recommend this place to anyone.

Yes, it's expensive
Yes, the service is crappy
And yes, the food is simply amazing!!
I don't understand this place. I watched multiple parties leave before being seated from waiting so long. I decided to seat myself then wasn't served. Maybe because I'm white?

Great frozen custard recipe. I ordered a regular vanilla cone although there are several choices. Service was fast and friendly. Three big dips on cone for 3.50. Parking lot a mess and doing construction on side street. Difficult out unless going out on right turn. Can eat outside. Wish I could go often. Perfect flavor for custard and no ice. Ramp to order window as well as a drive up.

Dumpy old place, high prices, rude service.  Don’t understand the hype.  Ordered a fruit drink and asked for custard in it and fully intended on paying extra for the custard.  Was told NO!  Made me order the fruit drink and the custard on the side in a separate dish.  I told them I would gladly pay for a side dish of custard and was still refused.  Idiots, rude!  Culver’s is better, cheaper, and will gladly customize an item to my liking.
Very nostalgic and great ice cream. Many flavors and types of ice cream and food. Great for families!
Not very good.  Service can be lacking and even rude at times.  Prices high for what you get.  Better than Dairy Queen but not nearly as good as Culver’s and much more expensive.

DELICIOUS!!! 
Pineapple sherbert and twist waffle cone we're awesome!

Great place, great atmosphere,  bland food. Been here several times for burgers.   Never really thought the food was great.   The atmosphere makes up for it though. Great Indoor and out. Just doesn't make up for the tasteless food though.
Food wasn't bad. My mom's shrimp weren't very good, the tasted like they might have been fried in old oil. The sweet potato waffle fries were cold. My roast beef wasnt bad though. Service was good.

I'm from out of town. Went there on a date. Ordered a Margarita and it was very small. Should've been a shot. Ordered the 16oz steak and it was 10oz's of fat and gristle. Nice lay out, but I'll never go their again
Classic restaurant with a great new space their buffalo sauce is the best in town. I always get the buffalo chicken pasta salad.

Great food, excellent service, and a classy atmosphere! Truly one of the best local options in the Greater Lafayette area! I really like their fries, in particular. It might be a sports bar, but definitely not overwhelmingly so as is the case with a lot of others.

One of the best restaurants in town and probably my favorite. I've ate here on a weekly basis for almost a year as part of a club. I never really had a bad experience. It has consistently good food, service and atmosphere. So many good memories are tied to this place for me.

Love this place. Great Wait staff and great brews on tap. Delicious food as well. Saw the Whiskey Belles there and they were outstanding. 
Ya gotta go here!!
Outstanding food. Incredible service. It doesn’t get much better than this. Love this place.
Great pub with a nice atmosphere and superb food. Much quieter and accessibility in the parking aspect than the westside one. Live bands on the weekends, if that's your thing.

If you're wanting a good meal and a nice beer, this is the spot. In my opinion this location is better than the one in W. Lafayette because the college crowd is not here, so there is actually some peace and it is not as chaotic. I've been here so many times and have never once been disappointed with my visit. They have live music on Fridays and Saturdays. You'll have a good time.

The place is sweet and sober... Their food is super delicious.. totally loved it.. And it was perfectly plated.. Also the staff is very well behaved... Overall a perfect experience.. Definitely going on my frequent places list..

Very nice place to hangout with family and friends.Noticed this place while roaming around and looking for some decent place for lunch and I was not at all disappointed as I entered this restaurant. Ambience is amazing.Staff is also very good.The best part is that the restaurant has outdoor sitting as well and also very well managed. Now coming to the food,the menu offers you a lot of variety. Ordered both veg and non veg dishes and yes the food was really delicious. Last but not least price is really reasonable.Must try place while in Prayagraj.
Really nice ambience. Good service. Waitress was quick and had knowledge of the good food. Food is good. Quick service. A reasonable, pocket-friendly restaurant.

Good food. Combos are affordable.
 Location is friendly. Should visit after sunset to get a better view of the place.
One of the best place... One of the best thing is that it has both the cafe and restraunt.. loved the ambience and food.. price is budget friendly..
Great little place! It’s kinda hidden from the road but the food is excellent! It’s a family owned business and I love how friendly the staff was
Tasty food for a good price!
Love this place so much! Prices are great and place is cozy!
Kibu is by far the best Korean restaurant around West Lafayette and Lafayette. The chicken katsu is to die for!

I really enjoy Kibu Cafe. It unquestionably caters to the local Asian student population. On weekends in particular, when the dorm cafeterias close, you won't hear a lot of English in the dining room... interestingly, there's a lot more Mandarin than Korean, but still.

You order at the window, and they bring the food out. Water and soup are both free and self-serve, which is a nice touch. You're encouraged to put away your own dishes.

The food quality is decent and plentiful. The staff is consistently friendly. We lean toward the spicy end of the menu. With kimchi soup, spicy squid and spicy pork, the menu gives plenty of choices. All in all, well worth a spot on the "Where would you like to eat tonight?" list, even if you're *not* an Asian Purdue student.

For the most part, Vienna has been great. However, today I bought some scones that were pretty hard/dry. Come to find out, not all the baked goods are fresh. I would recommend asking about the freshness of a baked good before buying it, because it's disappointing buying something full price and finding that it's stale.

I mentioned this to the employees working at the front, and there was little action taken to rectify the situation, which was more disappointing.
Great coffee shop. More relaxed than Gray House.
They have the best chai and good white hot chocolate 🙂

This quaint and cozy coffee house is extremely friendly and has an ambience that welcomes anyone who walks through the doors. I stopped while I was driving on route 65 N. had to travel about 15 minutes but it was worth the drive, the service was exceptional, courteous and the coffee was excellent also their prices are extremely reasonable.
The mocha freeze I got was really good! But the desserts were pretty mediocre and did not taste fresh. Would come back for the coffee but not the food.

As soon as I walked in, I was greeted with a happy smile! Although when it came time to order, I had to wait since there was only one person working the cash register (even though there were a lot more behind the register area although I am not sure what they were doing). I got the broccoli cheddar soup which was of course delicious and I sat by the fire. It was peaceful. I will definitely come back to this panera in the future!

They rarely get orders correct. Today my salad was missing the chicken, they asked if I wanted to come back to get it, really! Don't they teach their folks that prepare the food to actually read their computer screens? They managed to not put the red onion on the salad but no chicken.

We order from Panera on Reed Hartman regularly for our company lunches. Have always loved the food. Last time we ordered, there was a hair in one of our soups. Two of us ordered the same soup. Needless to say it really made our stomachs churn and ruined lunch for all five of us that had ordered. I called to speak to a manager. The woman that answered the phone was beyond rude. She had no idea what I was calling for and said "they too busy to speak to you". Mind you, I could have been calling for catering info because I had not given my reason for calling yet. When I insisted on needing to speak to a manager, the delivery manager got on the phone. I explained everything. She apologized and said "Your next delivery order will be comped. I'm putting it in the book." (I didn't ask her to do this.) So we called today to order and spoke to the delivery manager who said she could only comp the cup of soup. Since that is not what she told me, I asked to speak to the GM who proceeded to say that they can only comp the soup. I asked if they record their calls -- they don't. Picture of the hair in the soup below. They need to learn about good customer service because we ordered regularly from them not only for a few of us but for team lunches to be catered in as well and we will not be doing that anymore. I don't normally complain. I never leave bad reviews but this is ridiculous. I didn't ask for our entire order to be comped, they volunteered it and then didn't honor it.

Outstanding experience during the lunch rush.

The line was to the door, but the staff and management kept the service flowing and my food came out perfect.

Very nice facility with plenty of seating, much above average for a Panera. Well maintained and clean.
This is an ok Panera Bread. It's pretty much what you would expect. The place is nice, clean and the staff is friendly. Other than that there is nothing too special about the place.

This is a great place to quickly get some snacks while you're studying at tark or if you live at tark. You don't even have to leave the building, there's a great selection of snacks and drinks here. The service is great they can be really helpful and they are really friendly.
11/10 very good

Just like the one at home. They have huge screens and are a good size for large parties. They can accommodate a large group. Please call in advance for large parties. Good selection at the bar, all your favorite drinks and some local brew. I went back the next day and was treated just as good. I liked the service and the staff was really trying to get me everything I asked for.

The food is set by the company, and the back end fulfills their end of the deal by making great, casual food. However, the front end customer service leaves something to be desired. Too long to come back to table. Little menu knowledge (this has been on three occasions in the past month). If you want to watch the game and dont care about customer service, then 5 stars.
The patron was very attentive and very helpful. The appetizers were delicious and the pulled pork sandwich could have used less salt but overall good. There were no images due to the gobbled up food.
The food was good but what made the experience even better was our server!! She was amazing... just wished I could remember her name.  I would hire her in a heartbeat

Atmosphere is their main attraction. The wings are ok. Let's face it you go for the drinks and sports.  However the burger never disappoints.  Bloody Mary could use some tweaking.  I've had better. Can't mess up the draft drinks. Service is slow so order a drink before you get to the glass half-empty.

One of the best restaurants in town and probably my favorite. I've ate here on a weekly basis for almost a year as part of a club. I never really had a bad experience. It has consistently good food, service and atmosphere. So many good memories are tied to this place for me.

Love this place. Great Wait staff and great brews on tap. Delicious food as well. Saw the Whiskey Belles there and they were outstanding. 
Ya gotta go here!!
Outstanding food. Incredible service. It doesn’t get much better than this. Love this place.

Lafayette because the college crowd is not here, so there is actually some peace and it is not as chaotic. I've been here so many times and have never once been disappointed with my visit. They have live music on Fridays and Saturdays. You'll have a good time.
